02:09 PM Defendant Victor T Lucero in court with attorney Christopher Lee Hartley.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Niki Kane, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases called for plea and sentencing. 
State has complied with victim's rights. Victim appears in person.
State places offer on the record. 
Court conducts plea colloquy.

In case 22CF194:
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 3 & 4.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Counts 1-2 and 5-6 are Dismissed and read in.

In case 22CF421:
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Counts 1 and 3-14 are Dismissed and read in.

State and Defense make sentencing recommendation.
Victim A makes statement to the court.
Defendant makes statement to the court.

In case 22CF194:
COUNT 3:
Court orders the following:
IMPOSED AND STAYED: 

JAIL:  9 MONTHS in the Waukesha County Jail - Straight-time.
22  Days Credit.

TERM ON PROBATION:  3 YEARS; Court does not object to transfer to Milwaukee County; 
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Absolute Sobriety;  
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by providers at the VA; 
*Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling;
*No violent contact with:  Victim A or any other family member; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Domestic Violence Counseling through a State certified batterers intervention program;
*No use of possession of weapons (e.g. knives, firearms, etc.)

RESTITUTION:  TBD ; State to file a request for hearing to address within 10 days
COSTS:  $243
DOMESTIC VIOLENCE SURCHARGE: $100
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

*Cash on file to be applied to costs/fines/surcharges with the balance, except for $582.24 (Subject to restitution request), to be refunded to the poster.
*Upon Petition - Court will consider early termination of probation at any point after 2 years, if all conditions are met and agent deems appropriate.

